bin elevation greater than 2 times ULN, aminotransferase elevations are greater than 8 times ULN, or aminotransferase elevations persist beyond 2 weeks.', 'Synergism', 'The use of bedaquiline with other potentially hepatotoxic agents should be avoided whenever possible (e.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/103992/', '', 'Gemfibrozil, Evinacumab, Evolocumab, Dextrothyroxine, Cholestyramine, Clofibrate, Colestipol, Ezetimibe, Bempedoic acid, Colesevelam, Alirocumab, More', 'Capreomycin, Pyrazinamide, Rifamycin, Sulfamethoxazole, Rifapentine, Streptomycin, Trimethoprim, Rifampicin, Cycloserine, Rifabutin, Isoniazid, More', 1767369485);
